## Plan Summary

**Only one file needs to change:** `src/routes.ts`

The fix is a straightforward rewrite of the `GET /users` handler. Here's the approach:

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10;
  const total = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data  = users.slice(start, start + limit);

  res.json({ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } });
});
```

**Why this works for every test case:**
- **Defaults** — `parseInt(...) || 1` / `|| 10` handles missing or invalid query params
- **Out-of-range page** — `Array.slice` with a `start` beyond the array length naturally returns `[]`, no special guard needed
- **`GET /users/:id`** — completely untouched

No changes to `types.ts`, `data.ts`, or `app.ts`. All 6 existing + new tests should pass after this single edit.
